HEADWORD: oral surgery
<hw>o"ral sur"ge*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Surgery performed within the mouth cavity, especially that
performed around the gums and teeth as an expedient for the purpose of
preservation or replacement of teeth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

